1
00:00:05,671 --> 00:00:07,711
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,711 --> 00:00:09,141
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:11,711 --> 00:00:14,951
I know you wanted to move.
Too bad for you.

4
00:00:15,251 --> 00:00:17,351
You're enjoying this way too much.

5
00:00:17,681 --> 00:00:18,721
Is it that obvious?

6
00:00:19,891 --> 00:00:23,491
Woo Jae, honey, I'm so sorry
I didn't realize you were sick.

7
00:00:24,591 --> 00:00:27,631
You don't need to be sorry, Grandma.
I didn't tell you on purpose.

8
00:00:27,931 --> 00:00:31,101
But still... I always used to know
if you even had a slight fever.

9
00:00:32,001 --> 00:00:35,441
It's really nothing to worry about.
I'm fine.

10
00:00:36,641 --> 00:00:39,971
- Did Mom say to take a break?
- Yes.

11
00:00:40,511 --> 00:00:43,611
She acted like the world was ending
when I gave up becoming a doctor.

12
00:00:44,341 --> 00:00:46,351
That's because you quit for good.

13
00:00:47,051 --> 00:00:48,651
I'll work part-time for a bit,
then resume my studies.

14
00:00:49,251 --> 00:00:50,781
Don't set anything in stone.

15
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:53,751
Just go with the flow
and take it easy.

16
00:00:54,351 --> 00:00:57,761
You can't force things in life.
Everyone has their own path.

17
00:00:58,761 --> 00:00:59,891
That's true.

18
00:01:00,191 --> 00:01:03,831
When I chose design, I didn't dream
Mom would model my designs.

19
00:01:06,631 --> 00:01:07,931
What's taking her so long?

20
00:01:08,271 --> 00:01:10,701
It's her first time
visiting Ju Ah's office.

21
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:12,141
She wants to look her best.

22
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:17,211
- Here she comes.
- I'm all ready.

23
00:01:17,281 --> 00:01:20,751
- There she is.
- Wow, Mom, you're beautiful.

24
00:01:21,011 --> 00:01:23,181
- You look like a model.
- You think so?

25
00:01:23,721 --> 00:01:24,781
Do I look okay, Mother?

26
00:01:25,381 --> 00:01:28,321
Just "okay?"
You look so elegant and sexy.

27
00:01:29,261 --> 00:01:30,521
Mother, please.

28
00:01:31,521 --> 00:01:33,061
By the way, why didn't you go
to the morning workout?

29
00:01:34,491 --> 00:01:37,431
Why else? I didn't go because
I can't stand seeing your husband.

30
00:01:37,961 --> 00:01:39,371
Good for you, Mother.

31
00:01:44,241 --> 00:01:46,171
You're really quite vicious.

32
00:01:47,471 --> 00:01:48,541
What is it now?

33
00:01:49,311 --> 00:01:52,281
Wasn't it enough that you yelled
at Dad and said your piece?

34
00:01:52,551 --> 00:01:54,511
Wasn't it enough that
you and Grandma ganged up on him?

35
00:01:54,981 --> 00:01:56,621
But separating the beds?
That's so petty.

36
00:01:57,851 --> 00:02:00,221
Can we just go in peace and quiet?

37
00:02:02,321 --> 00:02:04,921
See? This is why Woo Jae
didn't tell you he was sick.

38
00:02:06,591 --> 00:02:07,761
That's enough, Gong Ju Ah.

39
00:02:08,031 --> 00:02:10,861
What? Only you were in the dark
when I was sick, too.

40
00:02:11,531 --> 00:02:14,071
How can a psychiatrist
and a family expert...

41
00:02:14,071 --> 00:02:16,001
not know that
her children are hurting so much?

42
00:02:16,241 --> 00:02:17,701
And then you go out in public
and preach what?

43
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:19,811
"Recipe for love."

44
00:02:21,411 --> 00:02:24,911
Do you have to push my buttons
on a day like today?

45
00:02:26,111 --> 00:02:27,551
Okay, fine. Sorry.

46
00:02:27,751 --> 00:02:31,481
Forget it. Since we're not moving,
I'm quitting the modeling gig.

47
00:02:31,821 --> 00:02:32,921
Cancel the contract.

48
00:02:33,291 --> 00:02:36,121
Okay, I'll keep my mouth shut.
My mouth is zipped.

49
00:02:36,191 --> 00:02:37,191
Zip.

50
00:02:38,461 --> 00:02:39,591
You little brat.

51
00:02:40,291 --> 00:02:42,161
Do you even consider me your mother?

52
00:02:44,861 --> 00:02:46,001
Well...

53
00:02:46,771 --> 00:02:49,701
Speaking of which...
When you get to the office later,

54
00:02:50,071 --> 00:02:51,801
could you please not tell anyone
that you're my mom?

55
00:02:52,671 --> 00:02:53,741
What?

56
00:02:53,741 --> 00:02:57,241
You're so well-known,
it makes things awkward for me.

57
00:02:57,911 --> 00:03:00,181
Just the director
and Jun Hyeok know.

58
00:03:00,181 --> 00:03:02,221
Don't tell anyone else.

59
00:03:02,681 --> 00:03:05,791
Fine. You're not
Han Seong Mi's daughter.

60
00:03:06,191 --> 00:03:09,121
You're Gong Ju Ah, born from a rock.
Happy now?

61
00:03:11,621 --> 00:03:14,031
When is your rebellious phase
going to end?

62
00:03:14,391 --> 00:03:15,701
When are you going to grow up?

63
00:03:16,901 --> 00:03:19,901
You're not exactly
a model of maturity yourself.

64
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:22,901
You just have to get the last word,
don't you?

65
00:03:23,341 --> 00:03:26,241
You should just never get married
and live alone.

66
00:03:26,741 --> 00:03:29,781
You'd drive some other family's
precious son crazy.

67
00:03:29,881 --> 00:03:32,581
So you admit
you're doing the same to Dad?

68
00:03:33,551 --> 00:03:36,021
I wouldn't treat my husband
like that.

69
00:03:36,721 --> 00:03:38,151
Look who's talking.
You don't even have a boyfriend.

70
00:03:38,581 --> 00:03:39,591
What?

71
00:03:40,751 --> 00:03:43,221
Seriously. Unbelievable.

72
00:03:43,491 --> 00:03:45,591
(Taehan)

73
00:03:45,891 --> 00:03:48,391
What was so important
you dragged me all the way out here?

74
00:03:51,101 --> 00:03:54,231
Don't tell me you two are finally
announcing you're dating.

75
00:03:55,131 --> 00:03:56,171
That's not it.

76
00:03:58,301 --> 00:04:01,971
I need you to keep it a secret
that my mom is my mom.

77
00:04:03,681 --> 00:04:07,551
- Is there any reason to hide it?
- I told you, I'm not comfortable.

78
00:04:07,851 --> 00:04:10,651
Don't you dare act like you know.
Got it?

79
00:04:11,521 --> 00:04:14,921
It should be fine as long as
you don't tell the VP.

80
00:04:15,991 --> 00:04:20,631
- You haven't told her yet, right?
- No, of course not.

81
00:04:22,031 --> 00:04:24,061
I'm going to head out.

82
00:04:31,341 --> 00:04:32,641
He's acting suspicious.

83
00:04:33,341 --> 00:04:35,711
You don't think the VP knows,
do you?

84
00:04:35,941 --> 00:04:38,681
Come on. If she knew, you know
she wouldn't keep quiet about it.

85
00:04:39,051 --> 00:04:40,051
Right?

86
00:04:41,451 --> 00:04:45,021
Anyway, I want your mom to like me.
Got any tips?

87
00:04:47,951 --> 00:04:51,621
I don't know what she likes,
but I do know what she hates.

88
00:04:52,261 --> 00:04:56,861
She hates showing off, bragging,
excessive compliments, or flattery.

89
00:05:01,231 --> 00:05:02,901
So, I should praise him nonstop?

90
00:05:03,171 --> 00:05:05,501
That's how you'll get Dr. Han
to look favorably on Director Yang.

91
00:05:05,871 --> 00:05:07,311
Keep praising him in front of her.

92
00:05:08,111 --> 00:05:09,541
Got it. Praise him.

93
00:05:10,181 --> 00:05:12,351
Let's see, what's there to praise
about Pacu Nacho?

94
00:05:13,851 --> 00:05:14,851
Also,

95
00:05:15,281 --> 00:05:17,451
I have something urgent
to pass along.

96
00:05:18,121 --> 00:05:19,991
Oh, what is it?

97
00:05:20,321 --> 00:05:24,761
Ms. Gong insists we keep it secret
that she's Dr. Han's daughter.

98
00:05:25,461 --> 00:05:29,161
- Why?
- For now, please do as she asks.

99
00:05:29,431 --> 00:05:30,431
Understood?

100
00:05:34,271 --> 00:05:36,841
It's a pleasure to meet you,
Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

101
00:05:38,801 --> 00:05:40,711
I look forward to working with you,
Doctor.

102
00:05:50,681 --> 00:05:53,591
I know you're busy,
so I just arranged a quick tea time.

103
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:55,791
Tea time is lovely.

104
00:05:56,761 --> 00:05:58,621
Have you been briefed
on the weekend event?

105
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:00,761
Yes, the One-Point Lesson.

106
00:06:01,631 --> 00:06:03,461
Will this be the first press event?

107
00:06:04,101 --> 00:06:05,101
That's correct.

108
00:06:05,701 --> 00:06:10,401
Oh, right. Our director here
has revised our brand story...

109
00:06:10,541 --> 00:06:12,301
to tailor it just for you.

110
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:14,611
For me?

111
00:06:15,241 --> 00:06:18,711
As discussed, we're restructuring it
into a charity event.

112
00:06:20,111 --> 00:06:23,551
That couldn't have been easy.
I'm very grateful.

113
00:06:24,451 --> 00:06:28,021
Thanks to you, Doctor,
we've found FG's true direction.

114
00:06:28,491 --> 00:06:31,361
I'm the one who should thank you
for inspiring our rebranding.

115
00:06:32,931 --> 00:06:35,431
To actually put that inspiration
into practice...

116
00:06:36,131 --> 00:06:37,301
You're really something else.

117
00:06:39,201 --> 00:06:42,601
Director Yang can achieve anything
he sets his mind to.

118
00:06:42,941 --> 00:06:45,001
He's one of the very best directors
in the industry.

119
00:06:47,141 --> 00:06:49,881
You seem to have a lot of trust
in him.

120
00:06:50,811 --> 00:06:53,081
Let's just say
he's my most trusted partner.

121
00:06:53,581 --> 00:06:55,481
We're both alumni
of the University of Buenos Aires.

122
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,521
So you two must be very close.

123
00:07:00,151 --> 00:07:01,221
Yes.

124
00:07:01,821 --> 00:07:05,361
There was this local bar in Palermo
that was sort of our secret hideout.

125
00:07:05,491 --> 00:07:08,831
When it was about to close down,
our Director Yang took that bar...

126
00:07:08,891 --> 00:07:12,901
and made it a small theater
with tango shows and dinner.

127
00:07:12,971 --> 00:07:14,831
He turned it into the trendiest spot
in the city.

128
00:07:15,671 --> 00:07:19,411
- I see.
- His branding was already superb,

129
00:07:19,711 --> 00:07:23,181
so I practically had to beg him
to come to Korea and work with me.

130
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:25,711
Ms. Hwangbo.

131
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:28,151
She has a tight schedule.
Perhaps, we should move on?

132
00:07:28,611 --> 00:07:32,221
But I have so many more nice things
to say about our Director Yang.

133
00:07:32,221 --> 00:07:33,291
No...

134
00:07:33,291 --> 00:07:34,891
Why don't you save some
for next time?

135
00:07:35,551 --> 00:07:37,161
Of course. Shall we go?

136
00:07:40,061 --> 00:07:42,261
- What was that all about?
- What?

137
00:07:49,101 --> 00:07:52,401
What's taking them so long?
Is their talk running long?

138
00:07:54,241 --> 00:07:57,781
Why do we all have to stand up
to welcome her?

139
00:07:57,911 --> 00:08:00,781
My family group chat went wild
when I said...

140
00:08:00,781 --> 00:08:02,551
I'd be meeting Dr. Han in person.

141
00:08:03,221 --> 00:08:04,721
I'm so nervous.

142
00:08:05,481 --> 00:08:07,391
Ms. Gong, you've met her, right?

143
00:08:07,691 --> 00:08:08,791
What's she like in person?

144
00:08:09,621 --> 00:08:12,361
What's to say?
She looks the same as on screen.

145
00:08:12,531 --> 00:08:15,731
I bet her family life is perfect,
don't you think?

146
00:08:17,701 --> 00:08:20,871
- I wonder about that.
- This is the Design Office, Doctor.

147
00:08:23,401 --> 00:08:24,871
Welcome!

148
00:08:27,011 --> 00:08:29,941
It feels like
I've walked into a fan meeting.

149
00:08:30,981 --> 00:08:33,381
I'm Kim So Hye,
one of the designers, Doctor.

150
00:08:33,851 --> 00:08:38,421
It's an honor you'll wear
the clothes we've designed.

151
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:41,991
I'm a huge fan, too.
I've seen every show you've been on.

152
00:08:42,191 --> 00:08:46,131
- Could I get your autograph later?
- Of course.

153
00:08:46,491 --> 00:08:49,401
- Doctor, right this way.
- Okay.

154
00:08:55,171 --> 00:08:57,201
Come on, lighten up.

155
00:09:02,641 --> 00:09:04,741
It's 38cm.

156
00:09:06,481 --> 00:09:08,211
- Are we all done?
- Yes.

157
00:09:09,051 --> 00:09:10,051
Oh, my.

158
00:09:10,351 --> 00:09:14,221
I thought Ms. Gong was the only one
with a perfect figure.

159
00:09:14,391 --> 00:09:16,391
But you're absolutely perfect too,
Doctor.

160
00:09:17,061 --> 00:09:19,831
You must take good care of yourself.
Right, Ms. Gong?

161
00:09:20,231 --> 00:09:23,631
Yes. We'll barely need
to adjust the pattern at all.

162
00:09:24,861 --> 00:09:28,431
It seems Ms. Gong is your boss.
You two get along so well, right?

163
00:09:28,771 --> 00:09:32,971
Of course. She has great style,
and she's so passionate.

164
00:09:33,071 --> 00:09:36,341
I like her so much
I even set her up with my brother.

165
00:09:37,081 --> 00:09:41,251
- You did?
- So Hye, about that main sample...

166
00:09:41,311 --> 00:09:44,181
- Could you bring me the work order?
- Right, sure.

167
00:09:51,721 --> 00:09:54,131
You're letting your coworkers
set you up on blind dates?

168
00:09:55,691 --> 00:09:57,361
That's enough.

169
00:09:59,701 --> 00:10:03,901
Anyway, about Bucket's son...
Is he dating the VP?

170
00:10:04,641 --> 00:10:05,641
Why?

171
00:10:07,171 --> 00:10:08,171
Why do you ask?

172
00:10:08,271 --> 00:10:09,281
Oh, well...

173
00:10:10,181 --> 00:10:14,111
It seems like something's going on
between the director and the VP.

174
00:10:14,351 --> 00:10:16,081
Wow, Doctor.

175
00:10:16,521 --> 00:10:20,021
You can really read people!
How did you know?

176
00:10:20,091 --> 00:10:24,291
Well, their familiar gestures...

177
00:10:24,361 --> 00:10:26,461
and the unconscious "mirroring"
of one another.

178
00:10:27,031 --> 00:10:29,331
It's more than just being close.

179
00:10:29,461 --> 00:10:32,101
I could almost sense
a deeper emotional bond between them.

180
00:10:32,401 --> 00:10:33,401
I know, right?

181
00:10:33,771 --> 00:10:37,041
Well, there are just rumors for now,

182
00:10:37,301 --> 00:10:39,741
- but I'm pretty sure it's true.
- Ms. Kim So Hye.

183
00:10:40,741 --> 00:10:41,871
I'm sorry.

184
00:10:43,581 --> 00:10:46,081
Ms. Gong, you're being
a little too controlling.

185
00:10:46,581 --> 00:10:49,451
This kind of small talk
at the office...

186
00:10:49,721 --> 00:10:51,081
is part of the fun, isn't it?

187
00:10:52,621 --> 00:10:53,721
You think so?

188
00:10:54,991 --> 00:10:56,161
Excuse me for a moment.

189
00:10:57,421 --> 00:10:58,561
Yes, Director.

190
00:10:59,631 --> 00:11:01,431
Yes, Dr. Han is all finished now.

191
00:11:01,991 --> 00:11:03,001
Okay.

192
00:11:04,261 --> 00:11:06,831
He said he's coming to see you off.
We should go.

193
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:16,041
Ouch, hot!

194
00:11:17,581 --> 00:11:21,251
Oh, no. Director! Take it off!

195
00:11:21,781 --> 00:11:22,921
Oh, no...

196
00:11:22,921 --> 00:11:23,921
Are you okay?

197
00:11:24,951 --> 00:11:25,951
It's burning.

198
00:11:52,181 --> 00:11:53,181
What happened?

199
00:12:01,351 --> 00:12:03,161
I think we've completely blown it.

200
00:12:03,421 --> 00:12:05,991
Why did you have to spill coffee
on Pacu Nacho?

201
00:12:06,091 --> 00:12:09,261
What about you?
What did you say to Dr. Han...

202
00:12:09,331 --> 00:12:12,101
that made her think
you two are a couple?

203
00:12:12,161 --> 00:12:13,171
Hey, now!

204
00:12:14,231 --> 00:12:15,631
This isn't the time for that.

205
00:12:16,301 --> 00:12:17,671
We need to go with Plan B.

206
00:12:18,141 --> 00:12:21,871
- We have a Plan B?
- No. Think of one.

207
00:12:28,251 --> 00:12:29,781
Will this be enough?

208
00:12:30,121 --> 00:12:32,051
I think you need to go
to the hospital.

209
00:12:43,801 --> 00:12:45,031
Here, let me see.

210
00:12:45,601 --> 00:12:48,901
Okay, good.
There are no blisters, but...

211
00:12:48,971 --> 00:12:51,641
Looking at the redness,
it seems like a first-degree burn.

212
00:12:52,601 --> 00:12:56,041
- It must really sting.
- My pride hurts more than my skin.

213
00:12:56,111 --> 00:12:59,451
Well, we should probably
put some ointment on it.

214
00:13:01,181 --> 00:13:03,751
Did Dr. Han say anything about me?

215
00:13:04,051 --> 00:13:05,051
What?

216
00:13:06,081 --> 00:13:09,621
Then again, there's no way
Bucket's son would be dating the VP.

217
00:13:10,321 --> 00:13:11,821
What makes you so sure?

218
00:13:11,991 --> 00:13:15,131
If so, do you think Bucket's wife
would keep her mouth shut?

219
00:13:15,261 --> 00:13:17,561
The news would be all over town
by now.

220
00:13:18,561 --> 00:13:21,471
Besides, I think
he might be into men.

221
00:13:22,101 --> 00:13:23,541
Mom, please.

222
00:13:24,471 --> 00:13:25,471
What?

223
00:13:28,071 --> 00:13:31,811
Oh, she didn't say anything at all.
She was in a hurry.

224
00:13:32,381 --> 00:13:35,211
Man, I really wanted
to make a good impression.

225
00:13:38,251 --> 00:13:41,621
You know, I heard that in Spain,
when you make a mistake,

226
00:13:41,721 --> 00:13:45,161
people say, "They must be in love."

227
00:13:46,291 --> 00:13:49,561
One hug would make me feel
a lot better.

228
00:13:50,301 --> 00:13:53,171
Hey, we're at work.
Let's keep a professional distance.

229
00:13:53,371 --> 00:13:56,671
- And I told you to use honorifics.
- I don't want to.

230
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,201
I'm in pain, so I'm just going
to talk however I want.

231
00:13:59,711 --> 00:14:02,741
What if you slip up
in front of the other employees?

232
00:14:03,941 --> 00:14:04,941
Okay, then.

233
00:14:05,911 --> 00:14:07,511
Outside of work,
we can drop the formalities.

234
00:14:08,211 --> 00:14:10,851
Gosh, seriously. Fine, okay.

235
00:14:11,651 --> 00:14:14,151
But you have to be careful. Promise?

236
00:14:15,121 --> 00:14:16,121
Promise.

237
00:14:29,331 --> 00:14:31,041
Aunt Se Ri, I'm home.

238
00:14:32,041 --> 00:14:33,441
Hey, Ji Hu.

239
00:14:39,341 --> 00:14:41,551
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

240
00:14:41,611 --> 00:14:42,981
I'll see you tomorrow.

241
00:14:43,951 --> 00:14:44,951
Take care.

242
00:14:44,981 --> 00:14:49,021
All right.
And for finding my pendant,

243
00:14:49,091 --> 00:14:50,491
thank you so much.

244
00:14:55,291 --> 00:14:58,001
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

245
00:14:58,061 --> 00:15:02,501
Hiring a handsome guy like you
was a smart move by the owner.

246
00:15:02,671 --> 00:15:05,201
Man, but now that
it's time to start,

247
00:15:05,201 --> 00:15:06,201
I'm getting a little nervous.

248
00:15:07,941 --> 00:15:11,211
By the way, that woman...
Is she an employee?

249
00:15:11,641 --> 00:15:15,951
- No, she's a part-timer, too.
- I see.

250
00:15:16,751 --> 00:15:18,951
But something's weird.

251
00:15:19,421 --> 00:15:20,421
What do you mean?

252
00:15:20,951 --> 00:15:23,291
I'm positive
I've never seen her before,

253
00:15:23,891 --> 00:15:27,361
but for some reason,
she feels really familiar, you know?

254
00:15:28,231 --> 00:15:29,461
That can't be right.

255
00:15:33,171 --> 00:15:36,171
That's what I'm saying.
She just feels weirdly familiar.

256
00:15:37,101 --> 00:15:39,071
It's like her vibe or something...

257
00:15:42,911 --> 00:15:46,381
Here you go.
Blueberry juice for brainpower.

258
00:15:46,981 --> 00:15:48,111
Thank you.

259
00:15:50,551 --> 00:15:53,821
Is something wrong?
You look so down, Ji Hu.

260
00:15:55,191 --> 00:15:58,321
I took a mock exam at my academy,
and my score was terrible.

261
00:15:59,521 --> 00:16:03,501
The academy moves way too fast,
and I'm struggling to keep up.

262
00:16:05,231 --> 00:16:07,801
With the new apartment complexes,
the school district has improved,

263
00:16:07,801 --> 00:16:09,871
so the academies
have become more competitive.

264
00:16:11,001 --> 00:16:14,041
- I'm sorry.
- Honey, don't be sorry.

265
00:16:14,741 --> 00:16:17,311
Is there anything I can do to help?

266
00:16:18,241 --> 00:16:20,151
You know, you're pretty amazing,
Aunt Se Ri.

267
00:16:20,581 --> 00:16:21,651
Why, what's so amazing about me?

268
00:16:22,151 --> 00:16:24,681
Honestly, I'm just your nephew,
so I'm basically a guest here.

269
00:16:25,051 --> 00:16:28,051
Eun Bin and Hyun Bin
aren't your own children either.

270
00:16:29,451 --> 00:16:32,361
- And?
- So how can you be so good to us?

271
00:16:34,961 --> 00:16:36,961
It's just...

272
00:16:38,501 --> 00:16:40,131
I guess it's because I regret...

273
00:16:40,831 --> 00:16:41,931
not having children of my own.

274
00:16:43,741 --> 00:16:44,941
You know the Korean word for "aunt"
contains...

275
00:16:44,941 --> 00:16:46,041
the character for "mother," right?

276
00:16:46,271 --> 00:16:47,471
Yes. Why do you say that?

277
00:16:47,641 --> 00:16:52,111
I'm not your son,
but I'll be like a good son to you.

278
00:16:53,281 --> 00:16:54,481
Oh, my.

279
00:16:55,751 --> 00:16:58,981
My goodness, Ji Hu.
When did you grow up so much?

280
00:16:59,051 --> 00:17:00,751
Thank you!

281
00:17:04,061 --> 00:17:05,721
(Onjeong Market)

282
00:17:06,261 --> 00:17:07,491
My gosh, you startled me!

283
00:17:07,561 --> 00:17:09,461
(I'm sorry.)

284
00:17:12,831 --> 00:17:17,671
(You are my savior!
Dong Ik and Jeong Han)

285
00:17:17,741 --> 00:17:20,871
Hey, what is all this?

286
00:17:21,811 --> 00:17:24,381
I'm on top of the world

287
00:17:24,541 --> 00:17:27,911
With the one who loves me

288
00:17:28,411 --> 00:17:31,551
- With my Jeong Han
- Will you cut it out?

289
00:17:31,651 --> 00:17:33,421
I want to cut it out

290
00:17:34,151 --> 00:17:36,321
- Cut it out?
- Cut it out.

291
00:17:36,861 --> 00:17:37,861
All right, fine.

292
00:17:39,161 --> 00:17:40,161
Here.

293
00:17:41,631 --> 00:17:46,131
Here, take back the member registry
and the account book.

294
00:17:50,741 --> 00:17:52,041
Hey, Jeong Han...

295
00:17:52,101 --> 00:17:54,541
If you're here to talk about
"Human Theater," just get out.

296
00:17:55,171 --> 00:17:56,741
What? Why?

297
00:17:57,281 --> 00:17:59,441
Hey, what are you
so bent out of shape about?

298
00:17:59,881 --> 00:18:02,311
Hey, thanks to me,
you didn't have to move.

299
00:18:02,451 --> 00:18:05,051
You kept the clinic,
and it all worked out for the best.

300
00:18:06,051 --> 00:18:07,051
Worked out for the best?

301
00:18:07,491 --> 00:18:11,291
Because of you,
Seong Mi almost divorced me.

302
00:18:11,991 --> 00:18:13,761
Come on, no way.

303
00:18:14,431 --> 00:18:16,391
There's no way
it was just that one thing.

304
00:18:16,561 --> 00:18:20,001
Your mistakes have been piling up,
and that was just the final straw.

305
00:18:20,301 --> 00:18:22,171
Why, you... Seriously...

306
00:18:23,141 --> 00:18:24,201
Hey, hold on.

307
00:18:25,901 --> 00:18:28,811
- Hey, you've lost your glow.
- What the...

308
00:18:28,811 --> 00:18:30,511
I'll give you
anti-aging acupuncture treatment.

309
00:18:30,911 --> 00:18:32,311
Hey, get off me!

310
00:18:32,981 --> 00:18:34,481
I have work to do,
so stop bothering me.

311
00:18:36,251 --> 00:18:37,281
Should I make you some coffee?

312
00:18:37,651 --> 00:18:40,591
Forget it! I'll make it myself.

313
00:18:46,261 --> 00:18:49,631
Please, you're being ridiculous.
Aren't you going to get up?

314
00:18:49,731 --> 00:18:51,461
That trick doesn't work on me
anymore.

315
00:18:52,061 --> 00:18:53,701
Your shoelace came undone.

316
00:18:54,301 --> 00:18:55,701
You're going to trip.

317
00:18:56,371 --> 00:18:59,501
Cut the act, okay?
Weren't you the one...

318
00:19:00,011 --> 00:19:02,511
who said nothing good ever comes
from being around me?

319
00:19:02,911 --> 00:19:07,011
Hey, is that what this is all about?

320
00:19:07,211 --> 00:19:08,211
Yes.

321
00:19:08,581 --> 00:19:12,151
Fine. Then tell me. What exactly
has gone wrong because of me?

322
00:19:13,251 --> 00:19:16,721
No, nothing.
Everything's been great.

323
00:19:17,061 --> 00:19:19,261
Gosh, it was a slip of the tongue.
Okay?

324
00:19:19,521 --> 00:19:23,131
Hey, even if
we've become mortal enemies,

325
00:19:23,301 --> 00:19:25,801
how can you forget every nice thing
I've ever done for you?

326
00:19:26,031 --> 00:19:29,371
What? Nothing good ever comes
from being around me?

327
00:19:29,731 --> 00:19:34,011
Oh, gosh, I'm a jerk.
Fine, I was wrong.

328
00:19:34,571 --> 00:19:36,781
You want me to write
a list of all your good deeds?

329
00:19:36,941 --> 00:19:39,081
Forget it, man!
I don't need any of that.

330
00:19:39,481 --> 00:19:40,551
- Out of my way!
- Hey.

331
00:19:40,811 --> 00:19:42,481
Hey, Jeong Han, wait!

332
00:19:44,151 --> 00:19:45,881
Man, that guy...

333
00:19:46,281 --> 00:19:47,691
Darn, he really knows
how to hold a grudge.

334
00:19:48,621 --> 00:19:49,821
Oh, boy.

335
00:19:51,761 --> 00:19:52,791
Yes, Father.

336
00:19:53,991 --> 00:19:56,731
What? Yes. I'm on my way. Yes.

337
00:20:00,031 --> 00:20:04,541
A certificate in retail management?
I didn't know this was a thing.

338
00:20:05,801 --> 00:20:07,171
Stepmom, come out here, quick!

339
00:20:07,671 --> 00:20:10,441
- Why?
- It's a total madhouse out there.

340
00:20:19,581 --> 00:20:20,591
Father.

341
00:20:20,951 --> 00:20:24,261
It says a pinch of salt
for every three eggs.

342
00:20:24,821 --> 00:20:25,821
You did put it in, right?

343
00:20:26,591 --> 00:20:27,631
What's a "pinch?"

344
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:31,831
No idea.
Am I supposed to pinch this?

345
00:20:31,931 --> 00:20:33,571
Pinch what? Who?

346
00:20:34,131 --> 00:20:36,841
- The salt?
- Yes, you pinch it.

347
00:20:37,201 --> 00:20:38,801
Like this, see?

348
00:20:40,541 --> 00:20:41,711
Hey, Dong Suk.

349
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:46,081
What are "fluffy" and "golden brown"
supposed to mean?

350
00:20:46,711 --> 00:20:48,611
Just wing it.

351
00:20:48,751 --> 00:20:51,751
Hey, "winging it"
is not in my vocabulary.

352
00:20:52,521 --> 00:20:56,621
- Oh, my goodness.
- Se Ri, is this the apocalypse?

353
00:20:57,661 --> 00:21:01,831
Oh, Father, honey!
I'm so incredibly touched.

354
00:21:02,861 --> 00:21:03,961
What's so touching about it?

355
00:21:04,561 --> 00:21:05,961
I'll do this more often, honey.

356
00:21:06,361 --> 00:21:08,701
Oh, wait.
We have to get a picture of this!

357
00:21:08,931 --> 00:21:13,041
Yes, send it to me, Eun Bin!
I have to brag to Hyun Bin.

358
00:21:13,571 --> 00:21:15,341
- My goodness!
- Come on. Let's take a picture.

359
00:21:15,341 --> 00:21:18,041
The biggest head is in front.
Wait, I should move back a bit.

360
00:21:18,981 --> 00:21:20,381
- Okay, taking the picture.
- Okay.

361
00:21:20,451 --> 00:21:21,611
One, two, three!

362
00:21:22,351 --> 00:21:24,721
One, two, three!
All right, a new pose.

363
00:21:24,781 --> 00:21:26,651
Yes. Dad, you look so cute.

364
00:21:28,021 --> 00:21:29,191
Grandpa, look over here.

365
00:21:35,061 --> 00:21:36,061
Yes.

366
00:21:36,731 --> 00:21:40,271
Wow, I never thought I'd see this.
This isn't photoshopped, is it?

367
00:21:40,901 --> 00:21:43,341
It's not photoshopped.
I took it myself.

368
00:21:44,241 --> 00:21:45,871
Yang Eun Bin,
what was your contribution?

369
00:21:46,601 --> 00:21:48,211
I did the dishes. Why?

370
00:21:49,471 --> 00:21:52,811
Son, I'm so happy.
This is all thanks to you.

371
00:21:53,751 --> 00:21:55,551
Hyun Bin,
are you coming home this weekend?

372
00:21:56,151 --> 00:21:58,881
I can't make it this week
since I have an important event.

373
00:21:59,121 --> 00:22:00,751
But I'll probably start coming
every weekend from now on.

374
00:22:01,791 --> 00:22:03,021
All right, bye.

375
00:22:15,631 --> 00:22:17,341
(Gong Ju Ah)

376
00:22:21,271 --> 00:22:23,811
Sorry, I left work
without seeing you.

377
00:22:24,181 --> 00:22:26,541
No, I'm the one who should be sorry.
The marketing meeting ran long.

378
00:22:27,311 --> 00:22:30,451
Did you see the ointment
I left on your desk?

379
00:22:30,921 --> 00:22:32,321
Yes, I brought it home.

380
00:22:32,951 --> 00:22:35,591
Make sure you put it on before bed.
We don't want it to get infected.

381
00:22:36,721 --> 00:22:38,461
Hey, why are you being so formal?

382
00:22:38,721 --> 00:22:42,361
- We agreed to drop the formalities.
- You're right. We did.

383
00:22:43,501 --> 00:22:45,961
Okay, apply the ointment before bed.
Got it?

384
00:22:46,461 --> 00:22:47,471
Got it.

385
00:22:48,271 --> 00:22:52,001
By the way,
I was thinking of pet names for you.

386
00:22:53,241 --> 00:22:56,611
Gosh, you're busy.
You didn't have to think about that.

387
00:22:56,981 --> 00:22:58,381
So, what are they?

388
00:22:59,011 --> 00:23:02,181
Okay, listen. Say "stop"
if you hear one you like.

389
00:23:02,711 --> 00:23:03,751
Okay.

390
00:23:10,891 --> 00:23:11,961
Jjua.

391
00:23:13,221 --> 00:23:15,861
Jjuring, Jjuyamong.

392
00:23:19,931 --> 00:23:24,871
- No good?
- I thought you'd be more creative.

393
00:23:26,041 --> 00:23:28,711
Hey, I'm not done yet.
Let's try again.

394
00:23:29,571 --> 00:23:30,711
Jjuataeng.

395
00:23:32,541 --> 00:23:36,851
- My Jju!
- My gosh, you know what?

396
00:23:36,951 --> 00:23:39,781
Yes, when no one's around,
let's call each other what we want.

397
00:23:40,621 --> 00:23:41,651
Yes, let's do that.

398
00:23:42,151 --> 00:23:45,021
But then,
what are you going to call me?

399
00:23:45,661 --> 00:23:48,431
Well, I actually haven't thought
about that.

400
00:23:49,291 --> 00:23:51,301
Think of one by tomorrow.
That's your homework.

401
00:23:52,901 --> 00:23:54,771
Okay. Now, get some rest.

402
00:23:55,101 --> 00:23:56,101
Wait.

403
00:23:56,601 --> 00:24:00,871
I forgot to tell Dr. Han one thing.
Can you pass it along for me?

404
00:24:01,841 --> 00:24:02,841
What is it?

405
00:24:13,421 --> 00:24:16,791
Well, I'm not doing the show.

406
00:24:16,861 --> 00:24:19,061
So, please, Mom,
don't be upset. Okay?

407
00:24:19,321 --> 00:24:20,691
You too, honey.

408
00:24:21,031 --> 00:24:24,031
Why not? We decided not to move
just so you could do that show.

409
00:24:24,101 --> 00:24:26,301
I don't know. It doesn't feel right.
You know?

410
00:24:26,631 --> 00:24:30,641
Our families are on such bad terms.
How can I do a show on friendship?

411
00:24:31,141 --> 00:24:34,671
It feels like
we'd be deceiving the audience.

412
00:24:34,941 --> 00:24:37,411
Couldn't you have thought of that
sooner?

413
00:24:37,781 --> 00:24:39,911
Come on, Grandma,
don't you start too.

414
00:24:40,281 --> 00:24:41,411
You're all going to give me
indigestion.

415
00:24:42,851 --> 00:24:44,321
Hey, I got a part-time job.

416
00:24:44,651 --> 00:24:45,681
What?

417
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:48,021
You did? Where?

418
00:24:48,491 --> 00:24:51,121
A barbecue place near the house.
The one we go to sometimes, Uncle.

419
00:24:51,191 --> 00:24:54,131
Right. Hey, that's great.

420
00:24:54,191 --> 00:24:56,031
- I'll stop by and see you sometime.
- Okay.

421
00:24:56,191 --> 00:24:59,031
Dae Han, how did your interview go?

422
00:24:59,431 --> 00:25:02,531
I haven't heard back yet.
I'll probably hear back next week.

423
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:04,541
I'll let you know as soon as I do.

424
00:25:05,641 --> 00:25:08,071
Mom, how was visiting
Ju Ah's work today?

425
00:25:08,441 --> 00:25:10,641
That's right! How did it go?

426
00:25:11,711 --> 00:25:15,811
So, wasn't everyone shocked
that Han Seong Mi is Ju Ah's mom?

427
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:19,381
- Right.
- It's a secret at work, Grandma.

428
00:25:19,581 --> 00:25:21,251
What? But why?

429
00:25:21,691 --> 00:25:24,361
I guess she's embarrassed
to be my daughter.

430
00:25:24,721 --> 00:25:27,261
Mom, why do you always have to
twist things like that?

431
00:25:27,531 --> 00:25:29,261
Dear, I see.

432
00:25:29,691 --> 00:25:32,201
I suppose it could get awkward
if people knew.

433
00:25:32,801 --> 00:25:37,101
Hey, Mom, they want you to come
to the One-Point Lesson as a couple.

434
00:25:37,571 --> 00:25:38,771
- What?
- As a couple?

435
00:25:38,771 --> 00:25:42,741
Yes. The VIP invites are for two,
so everyone's coming as a couple.

436
00:25:42,871 --> 00:25:46,381
They said it'd be awkward for you
to be the only one there alone.

437
00:25:47,411 --> 00:25:48,481
Forget it.

438
00:25:48,911 --> 00:25:51,081
As if your dad would ever cooperate
with something like that.

439
00:25:51,381 --> 00:25:53,791
Hey, I'll cooperate.
I'll do it. I'll be there, okay?

440
00:25:54,021 --> 00:25:56,651
I'll just postpone my volunteer work
at the senior center.

441
00:25:57,061 --> 00:26:01,491
Good. This time, actually be
Han Seong Mi's husband for a change.

442
00:26:01,661 --> 00:26:04,501
I get it. This time,
I promise I'll do a really good job.

443
00:26:05,331 --> 00:26:06,931
But wait, isn't that a golf event?

444
00:26:07,171 --> 00:26:09,771
- Dad, you can't play golf.
- Yes, I can.

445
00:26:09,931 --> 00:26:13,241
I used to play with the Onjeong
Medical Association Social Club.

446
00:26:13,341 --> 00:26:16,141
Exactly. That was 20 years ago.

447
00:26:16,571 --> 00:26:19,681
Hey, you think
I'd just lose my touch?

448
00:26:19,881 --> 00:26:24,251
I'm Gong. I'm good with a ball.
I just need to get that birdie. Pow!

449
00:26:24,551 --> 00:26:25,981
My gosh, how does this even work?

450
00:26:26,451 --> 00:26:28,021
Wait, what is this stuff?

451
00:26:30,051 --> 00:26:31,891
- For crying out loud. Hey!
- Oh, no.

452
00:26:32,321 --> 00:26:33,931
Well, hey.

453
00:26:34,331 --> 00:26:35,731
We've had this stuff here
this whole time?

454
00:26:36,231 --> 00:26:39,761
Yes. Director Lee Deok Su said
these were for beginners...

455
00:26:39,831 --> 00:26:42,131
- and gave me his used set.
- I see.

456
00:26:43,401 --> 00:26:46,141
But you know, your sister-in-law...

457
00:26:46,201 --> 00:26:50,011
She's actually talking to me now,
so if I play my cards right,

458
00:26:50,071 --> 00:26:51,281
she might finally warm up to me.
Right?

459
00:26:51,341 --> 00:26:53,581
Yes, for sure.
Go and score some brownie points.

460
00:26:53,651 --> 00:26:55,051
She's so scary these days.

461
00:26:55,181 --> 00:26:57,321
I get it. Just leave it
to your big brother. Okay?

462
00:26:57,751 --> 00:27:00,351
- Let's see here.
- Wait. It's been a long time,

463
00:27:00,351 --> 00:27:01,351
so take it easy.

464
00:27:01,421 --> 00:27:03,551
All right.
It's time to show off my skills.

465
00:27:03,861 --> 00:27:05,761
The moment I grip it,
it all comes back to me.

466
00:27:06,121 --> 00:27:09,061
Hey, I'll just rear back
and give it a good swing.

467
00:27:09,231 --> 00:27:10,431
Like this!

468
00:27:14,501 --> 00:27:16,431
What's wrong? Why? What is it?
Is your back hurt?

469
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:18,401
I pulled a muscle. Hit my back.
Pat it for me.

470
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:19,641
- Okay, let me see.
- My gosh...

471
00:27:19,641 --> 00:27:22,141
Hey, you haven't even started,
and you're already like this?

472
00:27:22,411 --> 00:27:24,611
Gosh, it hurts so much...

473
00:27:25,211 --> 00:27:27,881
Goodness,
who's calling at this hour?

474
00:27:33,851 --> 00:27:36,021
Hey, what are you doing?
Answer the phone.

475
00:27:41,391 --> 00:27:42,391
Hey, Hui Gyeong.

476
00:27:48,471 --> 00:27:50,101
Take care now.

477
00:27:52,141 --> 00:27:53,301
What do you think of this place?

478
00:27:53,601 --> 00:27:57,541
It's popular with many regulars.
I've shown it to others this week.

479
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:00,711
It is nice, but...

480
00:28:01,681 --> 00:28:02,881
I'm just not sure.

481
00:28:03,611 --> 00:28:06,251
I understand. It's a big decision
to make on your own, isn't it?

482
00:28:07,521 --> 00:28:10,251
Why don't you come see it again
with your husband?

483
00:28:12,961 --> 00:28:15,261
I suppose I should do that.

484
00:28:18,561 --> 00:28:19,901
(Ji Hu's Dad)

485
00:28:20,161 --> 00:28:24,771
Speak of the devil. He's worried
you're looking at places alone.

486
00:28:24,871 --> 00:28:27,111
- Go on, answer it.
- Okay.

487
00:28:31,211 --> 00:28:32,211
Hello?

488
00:28:32,581 --> 00:28:36,681
- Why are you calling?
- To finalize our divorce. Why else?

489
00:28:41,121 --> 00:28:44,321
The Certificate of Family Relations,
the Certificate of Marriage,

490
00:28:44,391 --> 00:28:48,661
and the Resident Register.
One of each. Here's my ID.

491
00:28:50,361 --> 00:28:51,361
And what is this for?

492
00:28:53,401 --> 00:28:54,571
Do I have to state a reason?

493
00:28:54,831 --> 00:28:56,731
Yes. The type of document issued
depends on the reason.

494
00:28:57,601 --> 00:29:01,641
- For divorce proceedings.
- I can't hear you. Please speak up.

495
00:29:05,541 --> 00:29:06,581
For divorce proceedings!

496
00:29:09,111 --> 00:29:10,111
Looks like he's getting a divorce.

497
00:29:14,221 --> 00:29:17,391
You'll need the detailed versions.
Shall I issue those for you?

498
00:29:18,061 --> 00:29:20,431
- Please do.
- Okay.

499
00:29:23,191 --> 00:29:25,401
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

500
00:29:25,461 --> 00:29:27,801
- Have a good day.
- You too.

501
00:29:31,841 --> 00:29:32,841
Dong Suk?

502
00:29:34,011 --> 00:29:35,011
You're here?

503
00:29:35,341 --> 00:29:37,311
Hey. What brings you here?

504
00:29:38,241 --> 00:29:42,051
- Getting my divorce papers. You?
- Me too.

505
00:29:43,681 --> 00:29:45,121
What do I need to get?

506
00:29:45,451 --> 00:29:46,451
Family Relations Certificate,

507
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:48,121
Marriage Certificate,
and Resident Register.

508
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:50,521
Thanks.

509
00:29:51,491 --> 00:29:52,961
Where do I get them?

510
00:29:54,031 --> 00:29:55,031
Over there.

511
00:29:55,861 --> 00:29:57,831
- See that clerk over there?
- Yes.

512
00:29:57,901 --> 00:29:59,901
- You can get them from her.
- Okay.

513
00:30:00,471 --> 00:30:02,401
- Thanks.
- Sure.

514
00:30:09,541 --> 00:30:11,441
- Dong Suk.
- Yes?

515
00:30:11,581 --> 00:30:12,811
Did you bring your ID?

516
00:30:19,621 --> 00:30:20,921
People ask all sorts of questions.

517
00:30:21,621 --> 00:30:22,621
Right?

518
00:30:24,161 --> 00:30:25,821
I'm sure they don't mean
to be like that,

519
00:30:26,661 --> 00:30:27,831
but it can be pretty awkward.

520
00:30:28,631 --> 00:30:31,201
And finding a place for my shop
is a nightmare.

521
00:30:31,761 --> 00:30:35,331
They ask, "Where's your husband?
Whose name is the lease under?"

522
00:30:36,101 --> 00:30:37,471
Just tell them straight up.

523
00:30:37,941 --> 00:30:39,341
There's nothing shameful
about getting a divorce.

524
00:30:41,811 --> 00:30:45,441
- Why help me if it's no big deal?
- Just because.

525
00:30:45,981 --> 00:30:47,211
I was worried you'd be flustered.

526
00:30:51,281 --> 00:30:54,391
Would you maybe... With me...

527
00:30:58,421 --> 00:30:59,421
With you, what?

528
00:31:00,891 --> 00:31:01,961
Never mind.

529
00:31:03,131 --> 00:31:04,861
What is it? Come on, tell me.

530
00:31:05,601 --> 00:31:07,971
Could you come with me...

531
00:31:09,731 --> 00:31:11,441
to help me look for a store space?

532
00:31:12,801 --> 00:31:13,801
Me?

533
00:31:15,011 --> 00:31:18,011
Never mind, forget it.
I was just saying.

534
00:31:18,081 --> 00:31:21,551
- I'm sick of everyone's opinions.
- No.

535
00:31:21,951 --> 00:31:23,211
I'll go with you.

536
00:31:23,851 --> 00:31:24,851
No, it's okay.

537
00:31:26,881 --> 00:31:28,421
It's something I have to get through
on my own.

538
00:31:30,121 --> 00:31:31,361
People might get the wrong idea.

539
00:31:32,191 --> 00:31:33,291
I should get going.

540
00:31:37,161 --> 00:31:38,701
I wouldn't mind if they did...

541
00:31:44,241 --> 00:31:47,511
Not this again...
My heart's acting up again.

542
00:31:55,451 --> 00:31:59,221
If you're sick, go to the doctor.
Don't just sit there like that.

543
00:31:59,481 --> 00:32:02,121
- Oh, dear.
- No, I'm okay.

544
00:32:02,421 --> 00:32:04,921
What do you mean, "okay?"
Why won't you go?

545
00:32:05,391 --> 00:32:07,631
Is it because when you see Nurse Oh,

546
00:32:07,691 --> 00:32:11,801
your heart starts pounding, right?
You rascal.

547
00:32:12,301 --> 00:32:14,201
(Police)

548
00:32:14,501 --> 00:32:15,571
Well...

549
00:32:18,501 --> 00:32:21,141
If I go to another clinic,
that would be...

550
00:32:21,211 --> 00:32:22,211
a betrayal, right?

551
00:32:22,471 --> 00:32:25,241
Yes, of course. Now, go on.

552
00:32:25,981 --> 00:32:28,711
If I catch your cold,
my mother-in-law will worry.

553
00:32:31,121 --> 00:32:32,351
Now, hurry up and go! Go on!

554
00:32:36,221 --> 00:32:37,691
That's why you should have been
more careful.

555
00:32:38,061 --> 00:32:39,791
- I know. I'm sorry.
- Come back again tomorrow.

556
00:32:39,861 --> 00:32:41,791
- I will. Thank you.
- See you.

557
00:32:42,731 --> 00:32:44,731
Mr. Gong, a package came for you.

558
00:32:45,561 --> 00:32:47,531
- But I didn't order anything.
- What?

559
00:32:48,031 --> 00:32:49,231
But it says Gong Dae Han.

560
00:32:49,531 --> 00:32:53,741
- "Pure and Innocent Shampoo?"
- Shampoo?

561
00:32:54,171 --> 00:32:55,971
Yes, that's mine. Give it here.

562
00:32:59,441 --> 00:33:01,811
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

563
00:33:11,921 --> 00:33:14,461
I love this scent. Here, smell this.

564
00:33:16,731 --> 00:33:19,101
What? It's unscented.

565
00:33:19,731 --> 00:33:22,031
No way. The scent is amazing.

566
00:33:23,301 --> 00:33:24,901
Man, it's so good.

567
00:33:28,571 --> 00:33:31,441
- What is it? What's wrong?
- This is...

568
00:33:31,841 --> 00:33:32,841
My heart...

569
00:33:33,981 --> 00:33:36,851
- Wait. My heart is...
- What? Your heart? What's wrong?

570
00:33:37,581 --> 00:33:38,921
It's pounding.

571
00:33:42,021 --> 00:33:43,791
Hearts are supposed to beat.

572
00:33:44,221 --> 00:33:45,691
If it didn't, you'd be a corpse.

573
00:33:46,161 --> 00:33:47,461
No, it's not like that.

574
00:33:48,561 --> 00:33:49,731
It's more like a stinging feeling?

575
00:33:50,191 --> 00:33:51,301
You know that feeling?

576
00:33:52,031 --> 00:33:54,071
Like something's burning inside.
It's hot.

577
00:33:54,571 --> 00:33:58,541
What's with you? Are you lovesick?
Did you fall for the shampoo?

578
00:34:01,071 --> 00:34:03,111
- Officer Jung?
- Yes...

579
00:34:04,681 --> 00:34:07,011
- What brings you in?
- Could I see the doctor?

580
00:34:07,081 --> 00:34:08,411
In love?

581
00:34:09,911 --> 00:34:10,921
Me?

582
00:34:15,021 --> 00:34:16,151
You're a little close...

583
00:34:24,901 --> 00:34:27,731
You've got a high fever.
When did this start?

584
00:34:28,171 --> 00:34:31,601
It hasn't been long.
It came on suddenly yesterday.

585
00:34:31,971 --> 00:34:33,041
What are your symptoms?

586
00:34:33,541 --> 00:34:38,441
My body feels really hot,
and my heart is just racing...

587
00:34:39,511 --> 00:34:42,981
Sounds like a cold.
And your heart is pounding?

588
00:34:43,311 --> 00:34:46,781
What? I mean, yes. My heart...
Not my heart. My lungs...

589
00:34:46,851 --> 00:34:50,251
My gosh, Officer Jung.
What brings you here?

590
00:34:50,451 --> 00:34:51,861
Are you sick or something?

591
00:34:52,191 --> 00:34:56,561
- Did you take his temperature?
- Yes, 38.5°C. It started yesterday.

592
00:34:56,791 --> 00:35:01,071
Oh, man. I bet you feel like
you've been hit by a bus, right?

593
00:35:01,271 --> 00:35:02,271
Yes.

594
00:35:02,771 --> 00:35:05,941
- All right, open wide.
- Yes.

595
00:35:06,001 --> 00:35:07,441
Wider now.

596
00:35:08,571 --> 00:35:11,981
Gosh, your tonsils are swollen
and pretty inflamed.

597
00:35:12,881 --> 00:35:15,711
Okay, I need to check your lungs,
so go ahead and lift your shirt.

598
00:35:16,111 --> 00:35:17,111
Pardon?

599
00:35:17,581 --> 00:35:20,421
- Lift it up?
- Yes.

600
00:35:20,621 --> 00:35:21,651
Just take it off.

601
00:35:22,691 --> 00:35:23,821
Take it off?

602
00:35:26,191 --> 00:35:28,491
(Pure and Innocent)

603
00:35:38,741 --> 00:35:41,241
So, this is love?

604
00:35:47,041 --> 00:35:48,051
Well...

605
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:51,151
I did lift it up.

606
00:35:51,551 --> 00:35:54,951
For crying out loud.
You have to pull it up all the way.

607
00:35:55,021 --> 00:35:57,251
- You're hopeless. Like this.
- No, wait!

608
00:35:57,691 --> 00:35:59,891
- My gosh, wait.
- All right. Hold on a second. Now.

609
00:35:59,961 --> 00:36:02,861
Okay, take a deep breath in.
A big one.

610
00:36:03,131 --> 00:36:07,571
And out. Okay, one more time.

611
00:36:08,031 --> 00:36:11,371
- Breathe in and out.
- Deeper!

612
00:36:14,441 --> 00:36:17,241
Okay. Fortunately,
your lungs sound clear.

613
00:36:17,711 --> 00:36:20,441
I'll give you some medicine.
Come see me again in two days.

614
00:36:21,451 --> 00:36:23,811
Nurse Oh,
go ahead and give him a shot.

615
00:36:24,111 --> 00:36:25,351
Make it a strong one.
You know the drill.

616
00:36:25,621 --> 00:36:26,621
A shot in the butt.

617
00:36:27,121 --> 00:36:28,251
- Got it!
- Great.

618
00:36:28,821 --> 00:36:31,291
- My butt?
- Yes.

619
00:36:32,891 --> 00:36:36,061
- Right this way.
- Wait, no. Please, Doctor!

620
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:39,261
- Anything but the backside, please.
- Come on.

621
00:36:39,331 --> 00:36:41,071
- Let's go!
- It won't hurt a bit!

622
00:36:41,131 --> 00:36:43,331
- Doctor, no!
- Come on!

623
00:36:45,741 --> 00:36:48,871
A cop who's afraid of needles?
Good grief.

624
00:36:54,211 --> 00:36:56,181
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

625
00:36:58,351 --> 00:36:59,351
Goodness.

626
00:37:00,121 --> 00:37:01,191
Officer Jung.

627
00:37:02,091 --> 00:37:03,091
Yes?

628
00:37:08,031 --> 00:37:10,791
(Eun Mi Hair Salon)

629
00:37:10,961 --> 00:37:14,971
I feel like you know all my secrets,
Officer Jung.

630
00:37:16,631 --> 00:37:17,641
It's a little embarrassing.

631
00:37:19,301 --> 00:37:20,801
Do you think so?

632
00:37:22,711 --> 00:37:25,111
You were the first to know
about my wife's affair,

633
00:37:25,881 --> 00:37:26,881
and...

634
00:37:27,811 --> 00:37:29,511
you knew when both our families
caused a huge scene.

635
00:37:30,351 --> 00:37:31,351
And also...

636
00:37:33,781 --> 00:37:35,891
You know about me
going to that motel last time.

637
00:37:36,391 --> 00:37:41,061
Are you worried
that word might get out?

638
00:37:41,131 --> 00:37:42,361
Is that why you were waiting for me?

639
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:44,261
Not entirely, but...

640
00:37:46,401 --> 00:37:47,401
Yes, that's it.

641
00:37:47,831 --> 00:37:50,201
Oh, don't you worry.

642
00:37:50,971 --> 00:37:54,941
It's my job to protect you.
I won't say a word.

643
00:37:55,511 --> 00:37:58,211
- Thank you so much.
- Of course. Don't mention it.

644
00:38:00,141 --> 00:38:03,011
But you said last time...

645
00:38:03,511 --> 00:38:07,621
that you met Ms. Yang,
thinking you'd never see her again.

646
00:38:08,121 --> 00:38:11,761
Well, if you're not moving anymore,
you'll have to keep seeing her.

647
00:38:12,121 --> 00:38:13,121
Are you going to be okay with that?

648
00:38:14,161 --> 00:38:15,461
It's just...

649
00:38:15,791 --> 00:38:18,401
I'm fine,
aside from my heart pounding...

650
00:38:18,401 --> 00:38:19,461
every time I see her.

651
00:38:20,331 --> 00:38:22,601
Your heart pounds, you say?

652
00:38:23,131 --> 00:38:24,171
Are you saying...

653
00:38:24,641 --> 00:38:25,671
Gosh, there it goes again.

654
00:38:26,441 --> 00:38:28,571
Let's say this is my heart.

655
00:38:29,171 --> 00:38:32,541
It's like it's completely fallen,
just like this.

656
00:38:34,851 --> 00:38:38,921
Oh, boy. Now, this is a big secret
that can't get out to either family.

657
00:38:39,021 --> 00:38:40,021
Tell me about it.

658
00:38:40,551 --> 00:38:43,791
I only felt comfortable telling you
because you promised secrecy.

659
00:38:44,221 --> 00:38:45,391
Officer Jung, by any chance,

660
00:38:45,821 --> 00:38:47,461
has your heart ever raced
for someone?

661
00:38:48,731 --> 00:38:51,731
Actually...

662
00:38:53,231 --> 00:38:54,831
Lately, I've been...

663
00:38:56,171 --> 00:38:57,171
feeling the same way.

664
00:38:58,671 --> 00:38:59,841
Really?

665
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:01,741
Yes.

666
00:39:04,241 --> 00:39:05,581
It's a really nice day.

667
00:39:07,281 --> 00:39:08,451
I guess spring is on its way.

668
00:39:09,351 --> 00:39:10,551
It sure is.

669
00:39:10,981 --> 00:39:13,781
It's the perfect season
for falling in love.

670
00:39:19,391 --> 00:39:21,231
(Damga Charcoal Grill,
Onjeong Market)

671
00:39:21,331 --> 00:39:23,131
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

672
00:39:27,701 --> 00:39:29,971
- Welcome.
- Welcome!

673
00:39:30,301 --> 00:39:31,871
Yes, right this way, please.

674
00:39:32,641 --> 00:39:33,641
Yes.

675
00:39:37,881 --> 00:39:38,881
What is it?

676
00:39:41,051 --> 00:39:43,951
Oh, you're just so full of energy.

677
00:39:45,621 --> 00:39:46,621
You think so?

678
00:39:51,891 --> 00:39:53,261
Hi, table for two?

679
00:40:02,271 --> 00:40:03,771
Why do I feel so anxious?

680
00:40:04,371 --> 00:40:07,301
I wasn't this anxious when Woo Jae
was just going to the study cafe.

681
00:40:09,511 --> 00:40:12,541
His shift is far from over.
Should I go check on him?

682
00:40:13,481 --> 00:40:17,151
No, I'll look too clingy.
Right, get a grip.

683
00:40:17,211 --> 00:40:18,981
Don't be pathetic, Yang Eun Bin.
Come on.

684
00:40:20,021 --> 00:40:22,051
Are you panicking? Yes, I am.

685
00:40:22,121 --> 00:40:23,551
No! What do I do?

686
00:40:27,421 --> 00:40:29,061
I could've made lunch in no time.

687
00:40:29,431 --> 00:40:33,301
Come on. Ordering in is much easier.
What's the big deal?

688
00:40:33,831 --> 00:40:36,531
Because it's not healthy for Father,
that's why.

689
00:40:37,531 --> 00:40:38,541
I was craving this.

690
00:40:39,871 --> 00:40:42,211
I told you
to get help for the house.

691
00:40:42,211 --> 00:40:43,311
Have you been looking?

692
00:40:43,571 --> 00:40:44,581
I don't want to.

693
00:40:44,911 --> 00:40:46,941
I don't want anyone else
touching my things,

694
00:40:46,941 --> 00:40:49,281
and I want to cook
for my own family.

695
00:40:49,551 --> 00:40:50,551
But you said you wanted to study.

696
00:40:51,221 --> 00:40:53,881
I can manage the housework
in between my studies.

697
00:40:54,221 --> 00:40:55,291
But, Dad...

698
00:40:55,751 --> 00:40:58,621
Are you really going to pay
for Ji Hu's tutoring too?

699
00:40:59,821 --> 00:41:01,331
If Se Ri thinks it's a good idea,
then of course.

700
00:41:02,461 --> 00:41:05,331
I arranged a meeting for next week
with a star tutor from Yeonjong.

701
00:41:05,531 --> 00:41:08,331
Gosh, really?
Wow, Se Ri, thank you so much.

702
00:41:08,431 --> 00:41:09,671
Thank you, Dad.

703
00:41:10,431 --> 00:41:14,371
It's unfair. Dad, why won't you pay
for my equipment?

704
00:41:14,471 --> 00:41:18,041
They're not moving,
so you have to keep your promise!

705
00:41:18,311 --> 00:41:21,081
That was only if Jeong Han agreed
to be on "Human Theater."

706
00:41:21,681 --> 00:41:22,951
That's so cheap.

707
00:41:23,811 --> 00:41:25,481
So Jeong Han doesn't want to be
on the show?

708
00:41:26,121 --> 00:41:29,451
No. He's sulking over a comment
and won't even look at me.

709
00:41:29,991 --> 00:41:31,521
That petty, small-minded punk.

710
00:41:32,261 --> 00:41:35,631
I thought he'd agreed
to stay and do the show.

711
00:41:35,831 --> 00:41:36,831
I wonder why he's acting like this.

712
00:41:37,161 --> 00:41:40,601
Apparently, his wife was so angry
she even brought up divorce.

713
00:41:41,101 --> 00:41:42,171
Gosh, really?

714
00:41:42,671 --> 00:41:45,841
She must have been furious,
but she acted so cool with me.

715
00:41:46,701 --> 00:41:50,311
I'll find a way to convince him,
so don't you worry.

716
00:41:55,651 --> 00:41:56,681
Try it again.

717
00:41:56,881 --> 00:41:59,651
Okay, feet shoulder-width apart.

718
00:41:59,681 --> 00:42:04,051
Keep my weight centered.
Then put my arms like this.

719
00:42:04,121 --> 00:42:06,921
Wait! No, I said to relax your arms!

720
00:42:06,991 --> 00:42:09,491
And stop twisting your hips!
Rotate your shoulders! Shoulders!

721
00:42:09,561 --> 00:42:12,261
I know! I was doing that!
Just let me be.

722
00:42:12,331 --> 00:42:14,161
- Then do it again. Come on.
- All right, fine.

723
00:42:14,161 --> 00:42:16,071
Okay, here I go.

724
00:42:16,601 --> 00:42:19,871
Okay, here I go! Let's do this!
Right, okay!

725
00:42:20,071 --> 00:42:23,311
Nice shot! I can't see it!
It's gone!

726
00:42:23,371 --> 00:42:26,441
Nice shot, my foot.
That was absolutely terrible.

727
00:42:26,541 --> 00:42:27,951
You're so bad at it!

728
00:42:27,951 --> 00:42:31,011
Because of you, your wife
is going to be so humiliated.

729
00:42:31,081 --> 00:42:32,821
- Is it that bad?
- Yes.

730
00:42:33,451 --> 00:42:36,251
Should I take lessons
for a day or two?

731
00:42:36,321 --> 00:42:37,551
Lessons? Are you kidding?
Give it here.

732
00:42:37,921 --> 00:42:41,091
Relax your hips and swing naturally.
Is that so hard?

733
00:42:41,161 --> 00:42:42,231
But that's what I thought
I was doing...

734
00:42:42,291 --> 00:42:44,701
Gentlemen, pardon the interruption,

735
00:42:45,201 --> 00:42:46,761
but you've got a golf coach
right here.

736
00:42:46,831 --> 00:42:49,671
You're a coach? Great.
Go give your lessons somewhere else.

737
00:42:49,831 --> 00:42:53,301
No, wait, Jeong Han. Hey.

738
00:42:53,641 --> 00:42:55,071
- Why?
- That guy...

739
00:42:55,811 --> 00:42:59,781
He's the Tiger Woods of Onjeong.
The Onjeong Market golf champion.

740
00:42:59,841 --> 00:43:01,041
Drives it 280.

741
00:43:01,411 --> 00:43:03,081
- Is he that good?
- Yes.

742
00:43:03,511 --> 00:43:05,721
I hear
you're in a couples' tournament.

743
00:43:06,181 --> 00:43:08,391
This is your chance
to get back on Seong Mi's good side.

744
00:43:08,721 --> 00:43:10,191
I'll genuinely help you out, okay?

745
00:43:10,791 --> 00:43:12,821
I'll zero in
on just the key points...

746
00:43:13,161 --> 00:43:14,791
and give you a crash course. Deal?

747
00:43:15,161 --> 00:43:16,431
Come on. What's the catch?

748
00:43:16,931 --> 00:43:21,371
You teach me golf, and in return?
You want me on "Human Theater?"

749
00:43:21,501 --> 00:43:22,501
Not at all.

750
00:43:22,831 --> 00:43:25,541
It's a purehearted offer
to help a friend.

751
00:43:25,701 --> 00:43:26,801
That's awesome of you, man.

752
00:43:27,341 --> 00:43:29,971
Hey, you're not in a position
to be picky right now.

753
00:43:30,041 --> 00:43:32,581
Just swallow your pride
and learn from him.

754
00:43:36,111 --> 00:43:37,681
- Don't be so tense.
- Okay.

755
00:43:37,751 --> 00:43:39,851
- Right, don't force it. Be smooth.
- Like this?

756
00:43:39,851 --> 00:43:40,981
Loosen up. Be smooth.

757
00:43:44,991 --> 00:43:47,361
Gosh, I just can't get this.

758
00:43:48,391 --> 00:43:51,301
- This is... Oh, boy.
- Jeong Han, my friend,

759
00:43:51,731 --> 00:43:52,901
your lower body, you see?

760
00:43:53,301 --> 00:43:55,831
How many times do I have to say it?
Your lower body keeps collapsing.

761
00:43:55,901 --> 00:43:58,771
My lower body is strong.
What do you mean it's collapsing?

762
00:43:58,871 --> 00:44:00,001
You're so annoying!

763
00:44:01,201 --> 00:44:04,211
Okay, fine, look. See?
It's good, but...

764
00:44:04,371 --> 00:44:08,411
Your backswing is perfectly fine,
but when you start the downswing,

765
00:44:08,651 --> 00:44:11,281
your weight stays
on your right foot.

766
00:44:11,281 --> 00:44:12,721
How many times must I say it?

767
00:44:12,921 --> 00:44:15,821
I've told you a thousand times.
I don't have a saint's patience.

768
00:44:16,021 --> 00:44:19,391
Okay, let's try shifting your weight
nice and smooth.

769
00:44:19,461 --> 00:44:22,431
Yes, "shift," you say?
Okay, I'll "shift" myself on home.

770
00:44:23,031 --> 00:44:25,661
Hey, all right. I get it.
Get back here.

771
00:44:25,961 --> 00:44:27,301
What now?

772
00:44:27,361 --> 00:44:30,271
Time for my secret weapon.
Now, feel it in your butt.

773
00:44:30,831 --> 00:44:33,701
On the backswing,
your right butt touches the wall.

774
00:44:33,771 --> 00:44:38,081
On the downswing, your left butt.
Got it? Okay, feel it out.

775
00:44:38,181 --> 00:44:40,241
- You want me to use my butt?
- That's it.

776
00:44:40,311 --> 00:44:42,411
So when I go this way,
my right butt...

777
00:44:42,481 --> 00:44:44,111
And when I go this way,
my left butt...

778
00:44:44,181 --> 00:44:46,321
- Hey! My left butt moves by itself!
- Right?

779
00:44:46,381 --> 00:44:47,381
- Yes.
- That's it! Now, you're getting it.

780
00:44:47,421 --> 00:44:51,321
- Good. Right butt, left butt.
- Right butt, left butt.

781
00:44:51,391 --> 00:44:53,561
- Hey, it's like magic!
- Okay, that's it!

782
00:44:53,621 --> 00:44:56,531
- Right butt, left butt, right?
- Yes.

783
00:44:56,591 --> 00:44:59,431
All right, here I go. Right butt...

784
00:44:59,831 --> 00:45:03,201
Left butt. Hey!
Did you see that? Did you?

785
00:45:03,271 --> 00:45:04,841
I'm a genius, aren't I? A genius!

786
00:45:04,901 --> 00:45:09,071
A genius, my foot. Hey!
You were meant to shift your weight!

787
00:45:09,141 --> 00:45:11,641
You can't do that one thing?
How many times do I have to say it?

788
00:45:11,711 --> 00:45:14,011
Are your ears plugged? You fool!

789
00:45:14,851 --> 00:45:17,511
Hey, see that?
Am I a genius or what?

790
00:45:17,581 --> 00:45:18,581
That was pretty good, right?

791
00:45:20,021 --> 00:45:21,451
Hey, was that good or not?

792
00:45:22,651 --> 00:45:26,491
Very good!
Wow, you've really improved.

793
00:45:26,821 --> 00:45:29,891
You really are a quick study,
Jeong Han.

794
00:45:29,961 --> 00:45:32,401
Of course. All I have to do is
swing this thing a few times,

795
00:45:32,461 --> 00:45:33,731
and I get the hang of it
right away, you know?

796
00:45:34,461 --> 00:45:36,631
I think I'm ready for a tournament.
Again.

797
00:45:39,671 --> 00:45:41,841
(Sample 1)

798
00:45:42,471 --> 00:45:45,241
The department store's revisions
are all set, right?

799
00:45:45,911 --> 00:45:50,311
Yes, we reinforced the stitching
and cleaned up all the seams.

800
00:45:50,911 --> 00:45:52,181
Thanks for working so late.

801
00:45:52,621 --> 00:45:54,621
It was nothing.
You bought me sushi, after all.

802
00:45:54,921 --> 00:45:56,321
It was so good.

803
00:45:56,821 --> 00:45:59,291
Right? It's a new place,
but it's pretty good.

804
00:46:00,321 --> 00:46:04,691
And since everyone's busy tomorrow,
I'll go to the buyer meeting alone.

805
00:46:04,931 --> 00:46:06,461
Wait. Ms. Gong.

806
00:46:07,461 --> 00:46:08,471
About the buyer...

807
00:46:09,431 --> 00:46:11,771
She's the niece
of Hyegyeong Department Store's CEO.

808
00:46:14,941 --> 00:46:17,571
You always have the latest scoop,
So Hye.

809
00:46:21,581 --> 00:46:23,481
By the way, Director Yang...

810
00:46:23,811 --> 00:46:25,621
I guess his marketing meeting
is running long.

811
00:46:44,171 --> 00:46:46,271
To the person I think of
whenever I eat something delicious.

812
00:46:46,571 --> 00:46:49,141
To my Bin, from your Princess.

813
00:46:50,311 --> 00:46:51,511
She did her homework.

814
00:46:52,241 --> 00:46:55,781
I like this pet name. "To my Bin."

815
00:47:06,521 --> 00:47:07,821
Did you enjoy the sushi?

816
00:47:08,161 --> 00:47:11,431
I did. It was to die for.

817
00:47:11,831 --> 00:47:14,231
How did you even think of me
while eating something that good?

818
00:47:14,831 --> 00:47:16,001
Is that all you think I did?

819
00:47:16,601 --> 00:47:19,071
I snuck into the conference room
to watch you while you worked.

820
00:47:19,341 --> 00:47:22,011
That's not fair, you got to see me.
Now, I want to see you.

821
00:47:22,271 --> 00:47:23,271
Come outside. Right now.

822
00:47:23,871 --> 00:47:24,981
What? Right now?

823
00:47:25,511 --> 00:47:26,511
Where are you?

824
00:47:45,801 --> 00:47:47,431
At this rate, you'll be
the flower shop's best customer.

825
00:47:48,531 --> 00:47:50,731
I figured I'd be visiting a lot,
so I got a rewards card.

826
00:47:52,171 --> 00:47:55,511
But look at the time.
You must be tired.

827
00:47:55,571 --> 00:47:58,311
It's a quick drive.
And there's no traffic at this hour.

828
00:47:59,741 --> 00:48:02,711
By the way, about our brand story...

829
00:48:02,781 --> 00:48:05,581
Are you changing it on purpose
because of my mom?

830
00:48:06,051 --> 00:48:08,081
I'd say it's thanks to her,
not because of her.

831
00:48:08,691 --> 00:48:10,921
You and your mother
gave me the inspiration.

832
00:48:11,921 --> 00:48:13,761
- Inspiration?
- Yes.

833
00:48:13,991 --> 00:48:16,161
Gong Ju Ah creates happiness.

834
00:48:16,731 --> 00:48:18,731
Dr. Han is someone who heals hearts.

835
00:48:20,701 --> 00:48:25,601
So FG embraces the hearts of those
who wear its clothes.

836
00:48:26,041 --> 00:48:27,041
Exactly.

837
00:48:27,971 --> 00:48:32,081
We protect your body's warmth
and keep your heart warm.

838
00:48:32,541 --> 00:48:35,211
Wear warmth and swing for hope.

839
00:48:36,411 --> 00:48:40,751
Dress the heart. Swing for hope.
Return to FG.

840
00:48:41,351 --> 00:48:44,291
My gosh.
You're a real marketing genius!

841
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:46,391
Way to go, my Bin!

842
00:48:46,391 --> 00:48:47,491
Gosh, you...

843
00:48:47,491 --> 00:48:49,631
I think I came all this way
just to hear you say that.

844
00:48:49,891 --> 00:48:51,291
All my fatigue just melted away.

845
00:48:56,701 --> 00:48:57,701
You scared me.

846
00:48:59,871 --> 00:49:03,471
- What's Grandma doing here?
- I was just doing the laundry.

847
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:04,941
But you...

848
00:49:05,741 --> 00:49:06,741
I can see that, you know.

849
00:49:07,811 --> 00:49:09,211
You can tell, can't you?

850
00:49:10,081 --> 00:49:11,081
Of course.

851
00:49:11,581 --> 00:49:14,051
Someone comes all this way
to bring you flowers this late,

852
00:49:14,421 --> 00:49:17,921
and you come in smiling ear to ear.
How could I not notice?

853
00:49:18,661 --> 00:49:22,191
Grandma, promise you won't tell Mom.
Okay?

854
00:49:22,761 --> 00:49:23,761
My dear Ju Ah.

855
00:49:24,191 --> 00:49:26,201
Is this your first boyfriend
in three years?

856
00:49:27,001 --> 00:49:28,401
Maybe I shouldn't see him then?

857
00:49:28,701 --> 00:49:30,801
What? Why wouldn't you?

858
00:49:31,671 --> 00:49:33,971
But you told me not to date.

859
00:49:34,401 --> 00:49:37,441
Hey, it all depends
on the kind of man he is.

860
00:49:38,641 --> 00:49:41,511
What's he like?
Just give Grandma a little hint.

861
00:49:43,311 --> 00:49:45,181
He's the one who opened up
a whole new world for me.

862
00:49:45,781 --> 00:49:47,751
He's the reason I became a designer.

863
00:49:48,351 --> 00:49:49,351
My goodness!

864
00:49:49,621 --> 00:49:52,421
Wow, that's not the answer
I was expecting.

865
00:49:52,761 --> 00:49:56,191
Oh, my.
You really like him that much?

866
00:49:56,531 --> 00:50:00,901
- I do. I like him so much, Grandma.
- Oh, my goodness.

867
00:50:01,401 --> 00:50:05,541
So what man has my Ju Ah so smitten?

868
00:50:06,641 --> 00:50:08,071
That's a secret for now.

869
00:50:09,511 --> 00:50:11,571
You should get to bed.
I'm going to head inside.

870
00:50:16,851 --> 00:50:17,851
Honestly.

871
00:50:19,821 --> 00:50:21,691
(Taehan)

872
00:50:21,751 --> 00:50:24,651
We've received the concept materials
for the PR article,

873
00:50:25,921 --> 00:50:27,121
so it looks like we're almost done.

874
00:50:27,621 --> 00:50:29,431
I love the new slogan.

875
00:50:30,761 --> 00:50:35,631
Dress the heart. Swing for hope.
Return to FG.

876
00:50:38,371 --> 00:50:42,771
This slogan explains perfectly
why we work hard on these clothes.

877
00:50:43,241 --> 00:50:44,671
See? What did I tell you?

878
00:50:45,311 --> 00:50:48,651
To make sure the people
who wear your clothes can be happy,

879
00:50:48,911 --> 00:50:50,711
I told you
I'd give it my all, right?

880
00:50:51,251 --> 00:50:54,821
- Our director's getting a big head.
- Hey.

881
00:50:54,921 --> 00:50:56,951
Hey, he's earned the right to.

882
00:50:57,751 --> 00:50:58,761
Director.

883
00:50:59,261 --> 00:51:01,791
- You weren't answering your phone.
- Right.

884
00:51:02,961 --> 00:51:06,061
I'm sorry about that. So, what's up?

885
00:51:08,831 --> 00:51:11,131
So the board members said...

886
00:51:11,601 --> 00:51:12,941
the charity event is a no-go?

887
00:51:13,371 --> 00:51:15,141
They say
we should only sell clothes.

888
00:51:15,441 --> 00:51:17,171
They're making a fuss,
calling it an ineffective expense.

889
00:51:17,271 --> 00:51:20,741
But a charity campaign's value
in securing loyal customers...

890
00:51:21,081 --> 00:51:23,681
is a strategy that's already
been proven by global data.

891
00:51:23,751 --> 00:51:24,981
It's not that they don't know.

892
00:51:25,251 --> 00:51:27,351
Their goal is just to interfere
with every single thing we do.

893
00:51:28,381 --> 00:51:30,751
Gosh, I can't just go
and confront Director Baek.

894
00:51:31,321 --> 00:51:35,931
Baek heads the Strategic Committee.
Does he have the authority for this?

895
00:51:36,091 --> 00:51:37,491
He doesn't have the authority,

896
00:51:38,291 --> 00:51:40,761
but he can exercise control
in the name of improving efficiency.

897
00:51:41,831 --> 00:51:45,841
Man, winning the contest would be
great news right about now.

898
00:51:46,541 --> 00:51:47,671
This is insane.

899
00:51:49,011 --> 00:51:51,781
It's hard to get anything done
when our hands are tied like this.

900
00:51:53,281 --> 00:51:54,441
I'm sorry, Pacu Nacho.

901
00:51:55,181 --> 00:51:56,751
I didn't think they'd go this far.

902
00:52:02,121 --> 00:52:04,121
The finish quality is perfect.

903
00:52:05,621 --> 00:52:07,491
Can I look forward
to some good news, then?

904
00:52:07,821 --> 00:52:09,331
Please wait a little longer.

905
00:52:09,631 --> 00:52:11,831
We'll have a clearer picture
after the Product Review.

906
00:52:12,131 --> 00:52:13,331
Yes, I understand.

907
00:52:14,001 --> 00:52:15,601
Oh, right.

908
00:52:15,901 --> 00:52:17,771
These are tickets
for our event this weekend.

909
00:52:18,071 --> 00:52:19,571
If you have time,
I'd love for you to...

910
00:52:20,871 --> 00:52:22,441
Sorry, just a moment.

911
00:52:24,911 --> 00:52:26,941
- What?
- What's wrong?

912
00:52:27,611 --> 00:52:29,881
I'm so sorry, but...

913
00:52:30,281 --> 00:52:32,781
it looks like the weekend event
has been canceled.

914
00:52:44,231 --> 00:52:45,731
What happened?

915
00:52:46,301 --> 00:52:47,831
Why was it canceled?

916
00:52:47,931 --> 00:52:50,401
They don't want to see
the ugly ducklings fly.

917
00:52:50,701 --> 00:52:51,801
Unbelievable.

918
00:52:53,171 --> 00:52:55,241
Director, are you okay?

919
00:52:57,611 --> 00:53:00,641
Let's start by contacting our guests
and letting them know it's canceled.

920
00:53:01,311 --> 00:53:04,551
The contest winner will be announced
around next week,

921
00:53:04,781 --> 00:53:06,681
so can't we just postpone it
for one week?

922
00:53:07,181 --> 00:53:09,321
But we can't be 100 percent sure
we'll win.

923
00:53:10,791 --> 00:53:13,721
And things don't look good
with Hyegyeong, right?

924
00:53:14,421 --> 00:53:17,991
The Product Review isn't done yet.
They said it would take some time.

925
00:53:26,241 --> 00:53:28,711
Ms. Gong,
what in the world did you do?

926
00:53:30,311 --> 00:53:32,841
- Excuse me?
- I'm asking you, what did you do?

927
00:53:33,041 --> 00:53:35,481
What are you talking about?
Ms. Hwangbo.

928
00:53:35,851 --> 00:53:37,011
Is something wrong?

929
00:53:37,581 --> 00:53:39,251
I can't believe this.

930
00:53:39,521 --> 00:53:40,751
What's wrong? What happened?

931
00:53:41,521 --> 00:53:43,021
Get this.
Hyegyeong Department Store...

932
00:53:43,551 --> 00:53:45,461
has decided to carry FG.

933
00:53:46,421 --> 00:53:47,421
What?

934
00:53:50,691 --> 00:53:52,461
Wait, no. How? Why?

935
00:53:53,201 --> 00:53:54,461
Why don't you answer that, Ms. Gong?

936
00:53:55,101 --> 00:53:57,731
Well, I just...

937
00:54:01,601 --> 00:54:02,941
I'm sorry to have to tell you this,

938
00:54:03,371 --> 00:54:06,041
but I've been told
the weekend event is canceled.

939
00:54:06,581 --> 00:54:08,411
I see. All right.

940
00:54:09,211 --> 00:54:10,211
Okay.

941
00:54:11,611 --> 00:54:15,791
By the way, who did you decide on
for the main model?

942
00:54:16,191 --> 00:54:19,521
We've finalized the contract
with Dr. Han Seong Mi.

943
00:54:19,661 --> 00:54:21,061
Wow. My uncle...

944
00:54:21,461 --> 00:54:24,361
I mean, our CEO
is a huge fan of hers.

945
00:54:24,661 --> 00:54:26,331
Oh, I see.

946
00:54:26,931 --> 00:54:29,431
But isn't this Dr. Han Seong Mi's...

947
00:54:29,731 --> 00:54:32,101
first time as a commercial model?

948
00:54:32,441 --> 00:54:36,041
That's right.
Fortunately, our FG brand story...

949
00:54:36,111 --> 00:54:38,611
really resonated with her,
so she agreed to do it.

950
00:54:39,511 --> 00:54:41,211
The brand story...
What was it again?

951
00:54:41,881 --> 00:54:43,511
Wasn't it pretty generic?

952
00:54:44,111 --> 00:54:45,281
Was it
the premium branding strategy?

953
00:54:45,581 --> 00:54:50,021
A portion of FG's sales profits
will fund mental health programs.

954
00:54:50,091 --> 00:54:52,161
- We've revised our strategy.
- I see.

955
00:54:52,621 --> 00:54:54,561
So the brand is donating
its profits?

956
00:54:54,691 --> 00:54:59,101
Yes. FG is more than just clothes
that keep you warm.

957
00:54:59,161 --> 00:55:03,531
By partnering with Dr. Han Seong Mi,
who heals hearts and shares love,

958
00:55:04,001 --> 00:55:06,871
we aim to also care for the hearts
of the people who wear our clothes.

959
00:55:08,071 --> 00:55:10,171
For example, something like this.

960
00:55:10,911 --> 00:55:14,941
We protect your body's warmth
and keep your heart warm.

961
00:55:15,381 --> 00:55:18,051
Wear warmth and swing for hope.

962
00:55:18,951 --> 00:55:21,451
Dress the heart. Swing for hope.

963
00:55:22,091 --> 00:55:23,491
Return to FG.

964
00:55:29,231 --> 00:55:33,501
I was only relaying
what Director Yang said.

965
00:55:35,631 --> 00:55:39,371
Our slogan apparently aligns
with Hyegyeong's values.

966
00:55:39,971 --> 00:55:43,971
And just like that, they'll make us
their premium section's main line.

967
00:55:46,341 --> 00:55:47,341
That's amazing!

968
00:55:48,851 --> 00:55:52,121
So, what does this mean
for our weekend event?

969
00:55:52,521 --> 00:55:56,451
What do you think?
We're in Hyegyeong Department Store.

970
00:55:56,951 --> 00:55:59,091
How could the board members
possibly justify stopping us now?

971
00:56:02,231 --> 00:56:03,661
Congratulations, Ms. Hwangbo.

972
00:56:05,091 --> 00:56:06,301
Good work, Pacu Nacho.

973
00:56:07,331 --> 00:56:08,561
Good work, Ms. Gong.

974
00:56:09,471 --> 00:56:10,831
But I didn't really do anything.

975
00:56:12,401 --> 00:56:14,801
Let's tell the Fashion Division
right now.

976
00:56:15,301 --> 00:56:18,411
Great idea.
They're going to go wild.

977
00:56:19,811 --> 00:56:20,841
Let's go!

978
00:56:29,191 --> 00:56:30,191
Are you crying?

979
00:56:31,951 --> 00:56:34,061
I could really use a hug right now.

980
00:56:35,631 --> 00:56:36,691
But I guess not, right?

981
00:56:37,561 --> 00:56:39,031
This is the office, after all.

982
00:56:39,461 --> 00:56:41,701
We have to maintain
a professional distance...

983
00:56:44,701 --> 00:56:45,741
Congratulations.

984
00:56:46,241 --> 00:56:47,801
You worked so hard for this.

985
00:56:48,341 --> 00:56:49,511
I'm so glad it worked out.

986
00:56:53,581 --> 00:56:55,481
It's all thanks to you, Gong Ju Ah.

987
00:56:57,051 --> 00:56:59,481
I'm just glad I could help.

988
00:57:02,591 --> 00:57:03,991
What am I going to do?

989
00:57:06,221 --> 00:57:07,261
Now...

990
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:09,661
I don't think
I can live without you.

991
00:57:23,711 --> 00:57:25,711
(Fitting room)

992
00:57:27,111 --> 00:57:28,181
We did it.

993
00:57:28,241 --> 00:57:30,181
(VIP waiting room)

994
00:57:36,621 --> 00:57:38,491
Why the long face, Ms. Hwangbo?

995
00:57:39,561 --> 00:57:41,261
Thanks to their synergy,

996
00:57:41,261 --> 00:57:43,961
we got into
Hyegyeong Department Store,

997
00:57:44,491 --> 00:57:47,961
but I still don't have a Plan B
to get them together.

998
00:57:49,801 --> 00:57:51,701
(Fitting room)

999
00:57:57,941 --> 00:58:01,841
Maybe we should focus on the reasons
they can't be together.

1000
00:58:02,251 --> 00:58:05,011
The reason they can't be together
is...

1001
00:58:08,551 --> 00:58:10,651
that their families
are sworn enemies?

1002
00:58:20,231 --> 00:58:21,801
Hello? Who's calling?

1003
00:58:22,061 --> 00:58:23,471
Yes, hello.

1004
00:58:23,901 --> 00:58:27,201
I should have contacted you sooner.
My apologies for the delay.

1005
00:58:27,641 --> 00:58:30,741
This is Hwangbo Hye Su,
the VP of Taehan Group,

1006
00:58:30,811 --> 00:58:34,641
and I also head up
the Fashion Division.

1007
00:58:36,651 --> 00:58:39,321
Oh, my. A VIP invitation.

1008
00:58:40,521 --> 00:58:42,891
Of course, I can bring my husband.

1009
00:58:44,291 --> 00:58:46,661
Yes, thank you for the invitation,
Ms. Hwangbo.

1010
00:58:47,521 --> 00:58:48,721
Yes, I'll see you tomorrow.

1011
00:58:52,401 --> 00:58:53,831
A VIP invitation...

1012
00:58:54,561 --> 00:58:56,901
To think I'm going to such an event,
all thanks to my son.

1013
00:58:58,771 --> 00:58:59,771
Hold on.

1014
00:59:00,471 --> 00:59:03,371
The VP of Taehan is a woman.

1015
00:59:07,681 --> 00:59:09,681
So, are you back for good?

1016
00:59:09,751 --> 00:59:13,281
No, just for a year.
An old classmate from Argentina...

1017
00:59:13,281 --> 00:59:14,651
asked me to help her with a project.

1018
00:59:15,481 --> 00:59:16,591
"Her?" So, a girl?

1019
00:59:17,651 --> 00:59:18,751
Yes.

1020
00:59:19,491 --> 00:59:20,491
Wait a minute.

1021
00:59:20,991 --> 00:59:24,591
The person who brought my Hyun Bin
back to Korea after 16 years...

1022
00:59:25,331 --> 00:59:26,331
is the VP?

1023
00:59:26,601 --> 00:59:30,831
What would you do
if I were actually seeing someone?

1024
00:59:32,501 --> 00:59:34,971
My gosh.
The person my Hyun Bin is seeing...

1025
00:59:35,641 --> 00:59:39,511
is Taehan Group's VP!
Oh, my goodness!

1026
00:59:42,211 --> 00:59:43,811
Oh, my, the VP?

1027
00:59:46,451 --> 00:59:49,121
Really? Ju Ah has a boyfriend?

1028
00:59:50,721 --> 00:59:52,921
I'm pretty sure it's a coworker,

1029
00:59:53,121 --> 00:59:55,091
so keep an eye out
when you go in tomorrow, okay?

1030
00:59:55,521 --> 00:59:56,631
Someone from work?

1031
00:59:58,261 --> 01:00:00,461
I didn't get that impression at all.

1032
01:00:02,471 --> 01:00:04,871
It couldn't be Bucket's son,
could it?

1033
01:00:05,301 --> 01:00:08,971
No way.
He only just got back to Korea.

1034
01:00:09,511 --> 01:00:12,781
Ju Ah said he's the one
who opened up her world...

1035
01:00:13,141 --> 01:00:16,011
and the reason
she became a designer.

1036
01:00:17,111 --> 01:00:19,281
It sounds like someone
she's worked with for a long time.

1037
01:00:19,921 --> 01:00:21,451
Was she being that dramatic?

1038
01:00:21,821 --> 01:00:24,991
Tell me about it. I was shocked.

1039
01:00:25,821 --> 01:00:27,991
I've never seen Ju Ah
look like that before.

1040
01:00:32,901 --> 01:00:34,431
Could it be Jun Hyeok, then?

1041
01:00:34,931 --> 01:00:36,401
You know,
the guy who started with her?

1042
01:00:37,571 --> 01:00:40,371
The one Ju Ah brought kimchi for?

1043
01:00:40,641 --> 01:00:43,141
Yes. He used to live
with his widowed mother,

1044
01:00:43,211 --> 01:00:45,171
but she passed away,
so now he's all alone.

1045
01:00:45,741 --> 01:00:47,011
Oh, my.

1046
01:00:47,681 --> 01:00:50,151
I bet he's the one
who's going to join our family.

1047
01:00:51,081 --> 01:00:52,321
There she goes again.

1048
01:00:52,781 --> 01:00:57,321
Ready to take in lonely people.
Aren't you a bit ahead of yourself?

1049
01:00:57,651 --> 01:01:00,021
But still, it's high time
Ju Ah got married.

1050
01:01:00,191 --> 01:01:02,731
It'd be great if she met a nice guy
while she has the chance.

1051
01:01:06,531 --> 01:01:07,561
Really?

1052
01:01:07,931 --> 01:01:10,471
The VP of Taehan Group
is Hyun Bin's girlfriend?

1053
01:01:11,031 --> 01:01:12,201
Wow. That's huge.

1054
01:01:12,901 --> 01:01:15,811
That kid... Would it have killed him
to tell us sooner?

1055
01:01:16,441 --> 01:01:18,911
I doubt that. I should ask him.

1056
01:01:18,971 --> 01:01:23,211
Don't, Eun Bin. The VP said
our visit is a surprise to Hyun Bin.

1057
01:01:23,281 --> 01:01:24,351
She told us not to say a word.

1058
01:01:25,111 --> 01:01:28,781
I looked her up online.
She's older than Hyun Bin, but...

1059
01:01:29,151 --> 01:01:32,921
she's gorgeous and looks so young.
Plus, she's an only child.

1060
01:01:34,121 --> 01:01:37,361
An only child?
If Hyun Bin marries into her family,

1061
01:01:38,031 --> 01:01:39,301
does that mean
he'll inherit the company?

1062
01:01:40,031 --> 01:01:44,001
Dong Suk,
let's not get ahead of ourselves.

1063
01:01:45,601 --> 01:01:47,571
Dad must be thrilled,
thanks to Hyun Bin.

1064
01:01:47,641 --> 01:01:49,711
You're getting a daughter-in-law
from a powerful family.

1065
01:01:52,511 --> 01:01:54,241
But this is a wild coincidence.

1066
01:01:54,241 --> 01:01:55,911
I was helping Jeong Han
with his form,

1067
01:01:55,981 --> 01:01:57,511
swinging away at the golf simulator,

1068
01:01:57,781 --> 01:01:59,681
and it ended up being
the perfect warm-up.

1069
01:02:00,321 --> 01:02:03,821
Everything's falling into place.
Honey, at your lesson tomorrow,

1070
01:02:03,921 --> 01:02:07,921
make Hyun Bin proud with your swing.
The Tiger Woods of Onjeong.

1071
01:02:08,961 --> 01:02:10,761
You're way better than me, though.

1072
01:02:11,391 --> 01:02:13,901
My Cha Se Ri,
who's even better than Pak Se Ri.

1073
01:02:14,261 --> 01:02:15,801
Honey.

1074
01:02:18,931 --> 01:02:23,171
There's a special guest tomorrow.
I wonder who it is.

1075
01:02:23,411 --> 01:02:25,711
I wonder. Is it a celebrity?

1076
01:02:26,181 --> 01:02:28,481
- Could it be Pak Se Ri?
- Oh, my!

1077
01:02:37,691 --> 01:02:39,721
Welcome, Dr. Han, Dr. Gong.

1078
01:02:40,821 --> 01:02:43,091
Oh, Bucket's son...

1079
01:02:44,031 --> 01:02:47,801
Right. The Director.
It's a pleasure, Director.

1080
01:02:50,271 --> 01:02:51,271
Jun Hyeok.

1081
01:02:51,931 --> 01:02:53,001
Yes, Doctor.

1082
01:02:54,541 --> 01:02:57,511
It's a pleasure to meet you, sir.
I'm Park Jun Hyeok.

1083
01:02:58,771 --> 01:03:00,441
Oh, Jun Hyeok.

1084
01:03:01,311 --> 01:03:02,581
My gosh.

1085
01:03:05,211 --> 01:03:06,321
Is this him?

1086
01:03:08,181 --> 01:03:10,291
It's great to meet you, Jun Hyeok.

1087
01:03:12,291 --> 01:03:15,621
Shall we head inside?
The event starts in one hour.

1088
01:03:16,391 --> 01:03:17,431
One moment.

1089
01:03:18,131 --> 01:03:20,531
The VIP I was about to introduce
has just arrived.

1090
01:03:21,101 --> 01:03:22,101
What?

1091
01:03:32,541 --> 01:03:33,541
What?

1092
01:03:34,141 --> 01:03:37,081
No way. What are they doing here?

1093
01:03:39,181 --> 01:03:40,321
Hey, son.

1094
01:03:46,961 --> 01:03:48,161
What in the...

1095
01:04:30,931 --> 01:04:33,841
(Recipe For Love)

1096
01:04:33,901 --> 01:04:35,541
- We're not even dating.
- Just relax.

1097
01:04:35,601 --> 01:04:36,971
- Our parents hate each other,
- You got this.

1098
01:04:36,971 --> 01:04:38,341
and you brought them together?

1099
01:04:38,411 --> 01:04:39,741
And Dr. Han, too.

1100
01:04:40,881 --> 01:04:42,911
My gosh, someone's getting jealous.

1101
01:04:44,051 --> 01:04:46,621
I'm Director Yang Hyun Bin's mother.

1102
01:04:46,681 --> 01:04:49,151
My, I was the last to know.
My goodness!

1103
01:04:49,221 --> 01:04:52,521
That jerk Bucket keeps teasing me.
It's so irritating.

1104
01:04:53,021 --> 01:04:56,661
"Dr. Han Seong Mi's husband
fighting the FG director's father?"

1105
01:04:56,661 --> 01:04:58,661
- Hey!
- Get this under control now!

1106
01:05:00,301 --> 01:05:01,631
You look beautiful today.

1107
01:05:02,161 --> 01:05:03,901
Thanks for asking me to hang out.

1108
01:05:04,131 --> 01:05:07,471
I thought today was going to be
the most miserable day of my life.

1109
01:05:08,972 --> 01:05:10,972
Dramaday.me
